about.summary: A collection of functions for interpretation and presentation of regression analysis.  These functions are used to produce the statistics lectures in <http://pj.freefaculty.org/guides>. Includes regression diagnostics, regression tables, and plots of interactions and "moderator" variables. The emphasis is on "mean-centered" and "residual-centered" predictors. The vignette 'rockchalk' offers a fairly comprehensive overview.  The vignette 'Rstyle' has advice about coding in R.  The package title 'rockchalk' refers to our school motto, 'Rock Chalk Jayhawk, Go K.U.'.

name: r-rockchalk
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.8.144' %}

{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-rockchalk
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/rockchalk_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/rockchalk/rockchalk_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: cb5e6c87ec95589f2b02da7ed7a5a67ec125e132100c8ae6762fad52820db71d

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]

  host:
    - r-base
    - r-mass
    - r-cardata
    - r-kutils
    - r-lme4

  run:
    - r-base
    - r-mass
    - r-cardata
    - r-kutils
    - r-lme4

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('rockchalk')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('rockchalk')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=rockchalk
  license: GPL-3.0-or-later
  summary: A collection of functions for interpretation and presentation of regression analysis.  These
    functions are used to produce the statistics lectures in <http://pj.freefaculty.org/guides>.
    Includes regression diagnostics, regression tables, and plots of interactions and
    "moderator" variables. The emphasis is on "mean-centered" and "residual-centered"
    predictors. The vignette 'rockchalk' offers a fairly comprehensive overview.  The
    vignette 'Rstyle' has advice about coding in R.  The package title 'rockchalk' refers
    to our school motto, 'Rock Chalk Jayhawk, Go K.U.'.

  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - izahn
